CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 24, 1956, pg. A35, reads: "Concert Soloists - Left to right, Maxine Brown and Carol Tucker, pianists; Murray Levith, violinist, and Randall F. Peters Jr. (absent), will be the principal soloists for the final Youth Concert of the season, March 24, at Stephen Foster Memorial Hall, 8:30 P. M. Tickets may be secured from Agnes O'Connor, 6412 Darlington Road. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Youth Concert soloists Maxine Brown and Carol Tucker at piano and Murray Levith with violin, posed at Stephen Foster Memorial Hall, Oakland
